textAfterTable: « Prev 3 of 17 Next » Arizona Cardinals at St. Louis Rams Dilip Vishwanat/Getty Images B/R Consensus: Cardinals (7-4) Vegas: Cardinals (-2.5)   Schottey: Cardinals Sam Bradford has zero protection, and the Cardinals have stymied better QBs with better lines this season. This win might not be pretty, but the Arizona D leads them to 5-0.   Miller: Rams The Cardinals' luck has to run out sometime. Right? The Rams are tough at home, and they have the right mix of hard-hitting defense and efficient offense to get an early lead against Arizona and hold on for a win.   Nagler: Cardinals If it wasn't for the fact that it will be played in a dome, this game would resemble an old-school blood-and-guts battle. First one to 13 wins.   Langland: Rams The Rams look relatively unbeatable at home, even when they don't score an offensive touchdown. This is the week Arizona's undefeated streak finally ends.
